Later on you meet both Boulet, Augustin and Anne-Marie at the edge of their property to discuss the matter of payment. 

Augustin digs into his coat pocket, already frowning, the way he does when money is involved. Anne-Marie has her purse out before he finds what he's looking for. 

“How much do we owe you?”

You look at them both. You know the Boulet are not wealthy. But then again, neither are you. 

