:: JobFinalModerate {"position":"4925,550","size":"100,100"}
"A couple of coin should suffice”

Anne-Marie hesitates, purse still open in her hands. “Are you sure? I could give you more”

"No, no." You wave it off. "It's fine."

She doesn't look entirely convinced, but folds the purse shut with the quiet grace of someone who knows better than to push. You close your fingers around the coins.

Not much. But if you haggle right at the market, it might just be enough to finally replace those awful morning clothes.

