:: Relationships [menu] {"position":"250,300","size":"100,100"}
<span class="typed-text">Louisette "Lou" Valet, //the Inn Keeper//</span>
<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ValantineD/Interactive_fiction_beast_of_gevaudan/refs/heads/main/pics/9hzli7V6.jpg">
Lou is somewhere around your age, though she carries it easier than you do, or at least makes it look that way. Ginger curls that she wrestles into a bun every morning and loses that battle by noon. Green-Blue eyes, a face full of freckles that the firelight catches in the evenings, and a dimple on her left cheek that only appears when she's really smiling, which is often.

You met her a few years ago when you first arrived in Tierce-Lieux, half-hollow and not particularly good company. She talked. You listened. Somewhere in the middle of that, without either of you making a decision about it, she became the one constant you hadn't planned on.

She runs the inn like she built it with her own hands, which for all intents and purposes she might as well have. She knows everyone in the village, their business, their feuds, their soft spots and keeps it all behind those sea-green eyes with a discretion that would surprise people if they thought about it.
She doesn't know everything about you though. 

Not even close.

But she knows enough, and she stayed anyway.

