:: doctor13 [Doctor] {"position":"4550,350","size":"100,100"}
“She will be fine. She needs rest.”

You hear Anne-Marie exhale slowly as you turn towards her.

“The illness has taken root in her lungs” You say as you rummage through your bag, for breathing-Poultice which you take out and hand to her 
“Apply this to her back and torso twice her day it should help her breathe better. After that I'm afraid only time will tell.”

Maybe bloodletting would work better, but you've never been a fan of the practice, Human blood tends to leave you with a queer feeling. You always thought it was due to being a werewolf, but $grandma was totally fine with it. So it's probably a you thing.

Anne-Marie inspect you for a second, seemingly looking to see if you tell the truth, but then relax slightly

“Thank you, $mc ”

[[“Of course”|JobFinal]]


:: doctor2.5 {"position":"3550,350","size":"100,100"}
	You see the eldest of the Boulet twins. Élise. She's no more than 15 winters. Tall, with the thick brows of her father, crooked nose of her mother but gentle smile that is all of her own . 
	Usually she's found helping out her mother, she made you a few tarts in the past few years. The first few one were a bit atrocious but she, thankfully, quickly got better. You're pretty sure she's been harboring some sort of hero crush on you. You cannot fathom why. Still, because of it she seems to have gotten a genuine interest in the culinary art. 
    
 	Lou is fond of her, so you suspect that soon enough she'll get a proper job at the inn.  
She's considered by the entire village as the eldest because of how responsible she is. Although you personally rarely see that side of her.
  
[[Next.|doctor4]]




:: doctor4 [Doctor] {"position":"3675,350","size":"100,100"}
"Is everything alright, dear? you look like you've seen a ghost."

You feel yourself tense before you can stop it, something cold tightening in your chest. She must catch it, because her expression softens immediately.

"My apologies, it is none of my buisiness." She waves it away gently. "We are simply here because the little one is sick again. Could we spare some of your time?"

You nod.

But before she can open her mouth, you hear Elise blurting out.

"Are you okay ?"

You turn to find her watching you, with the particular directness children haven't learned to disguise yet. It's still odd to you, to be the center of someone else's attention like that. For so long it was just you and your grandma, a small quiet world with no one looking too closely. 

You must look terrible. You know you must.

But then, you see her turning her head back at the road waiting for your answer. Whatever she saw, she's way too polite, too kind, to comment on it. 

You sigh. 

//How long can you keep this up? //

[[”I'm fine.”|doctor5]]




:: doctor5 [Doctor] {"position":"3800,350","size":"100,100"}
“I’m fine” you snip, words sounding harsher than you meant.

Your reaction surprises her. You watch it cross her face, the confusion, then the blush, then the dawning realization that she's stumbled into something too personal. For a moment she looks like she'd very much like to disappear into the nearby forest.

Augustin frowns at you.

//Damn it. //

It's not her fault. None of this is her fault. She's been nothing but kind to you, and here you are, bristling like a wounded animal at a child asking a simple question. You have secrets and no one to carry them with, but that's your burden, not hers.

You make an effort. It costs you something small, but you make it. You consciously unclench your jaw, letting the tension bleed out of your shoulders. You can do this. You can be a person for five minutes.

You exhale, and feel yourself soften. 

That's when you notice she's been holding something behind her back.

"Whatcha got here?"

Her whole face changes. The embarrassment evaporates instantly, replaced by something luminous and proud, as she hoists a pie above her head with both hands like she's presenting a trophy.

"I baked you a pie!"

[[”Really? What kind?”|doctor6]]


:: doctor6 {"position":"3925,350","size":"100,100"}
	She stands up a little straighter. "Blueberry!"

"Blueberry." You look down at it. Still warm, by the feel of it, the crust golden and a little asymmetrical in the way of something made with great enthusiasm and developing skill.
You tuck the pie under your arm before she can offer to carry it inside for you or, worse, suggest you share it right now.

"Thank you, Elise. Really." You mean it, despite yourself.

	You see her cheeks flush and suppress a sigh.

	You know how it goes with kids. They pick an adult, decide that adult is somehow worthy of their admiration, and there's that. You still have no idea what you did to make her choose //you// of all people. At first you assumed it was novelty, the new face in a small village, but that was years ago and she hasn't grown out of it yet. You live in hope.

	You wonder, not for the first time, what she'd think if she could see you as you really are. Half-naked at dawn, caked in mud and worse, crouched over something small and dead on the ground. 
    //Still think I'm so impressive then?//

	Still. It's not hurting anyone. And you'd rather not be the reason a kid's feelings get stepped on just because you're not comfortable being looked at like that.

	You cast around for a redirect before she gets any more attached to this conversation.

[[”How's your father?”|doctor7]]


:: doctor7 [Doctor] {"position":"4050,350","size":"100,100"}
"Oh! Well" She seems surprised. "Father is good, the lock holding the barn broke last night and he's trying to fix it I think."

You hear Anne-Marie hums. "I'm more worried about Jeanne" 

"Jeanne? Please mother, we all know she probably found some berries in the woods and is too busy eating them rather than actually working." She says, rolling her eyes.

"Elise." Anne-Marie says her name ever so calmly which, to your surprise, seems to calm down the vitriol the youngling had for her sister.

"Why? What happened to Jeanne?" You ask, and you can see Elise thank you silently for taking the attention off of her.

"Oh, well she went on a walk with our dog yesterday morning, but neither came back."

It is not unusual. Jeanne, while being a very sweet child, always had her head in the clouds. You often found her napping next to a tree, or simply taking care of the animals lost in time. She befriended a badger once, before it scratched her hand, which you bandaged.

"Im sure she is fine, like your daughter said, she probably simply lost track of time"

"Of course" you hear the mother reply, although her smile doesn't quite reach her eyes "I'm probably just worrying over nothing."

[[Next.|doctor8]]


:: doctor8 {"position":"4175,350","size":"100,100"}
Thankfully you don't have to think of an answer as you arrive at the Boulet's House. It's nothing extravagant, just a two stories house, made with grayish white stones and black slates for roofs. There is a barn close enough for the sheep.

You see Anne-Marie's husband, Augustin Boulet next to the latter. He is an older man, skin tanned from work spend outside, auburn hair with a few hints of white hair, a full beard and and darke eyes hidden under a stern look with frowned bushy brows. He’s the local shepherd of sheep in the village.
He seems to be focusing on repairing the lock of the door. From a glance, you're not sure he's succeeding at fixing it. He seems to notice you as he looks up from what he's doing.

You wave, and he nods, not one to talk.

You've never really entered the Boulets household before. All of them feeling well enough to come directly to your house in their time of need. Even when you helped Anne-Marie give birth, she surprised you when she knocked on your house after her water broke.

The house smells of fresh bread. And olive. The second one, you suspect, is the family's soap, as all of them carry this fragrance. There is a hint of sheep though. If you didn't know before, you'd knew by smell that this is a family of shepherds.
 
[[Next.|doctor11]]


