:: tavernfinal {"position":"6400,425","size":"100,100"}
You try to peer outside, squinting through the window, trying to read what's wrong. If you were a wolf right now your ears would be pinned forward, every sense straining. 

Then you hear loud, frantic knocking on the door. 

"<<if $doctor >> PHYSICIAN! <<else>>FATHER! <<endif>> HELP ME!"

“What's going on?” Lou is already on her feet, moving towards the door before the words are out of her mouth.

She pulls it open.

"My girl my sweet girl—"

Augustin Boulet stands in the middle of the street, wild-eyed and barely holding himself together, clutching something bundled tight in a thick blanket to his chest. The blanket shifts and you see it.

A small arm, hanging limp, streaked with blood.

You go very still as you hear Lou gasps.

The other villagers have gathered, some craning for a look, others reaching for Augustin, trying to anchor him to something.

"Augustin my friend, you must calm—"

"No !"  He pulls away, voice cracking open.  "You dont understand my Jeanne, my sweet little girl, she's been attacked!"

The realisation sparks within you like fire thrown on oil.

Last night.  The blood caked beneath your nails when you came back to yourself. The iron taste at the back of your throat that you'd tried not to think about. The flashes you can't quite hold, can't quite look at directly.

Teeth. //Soft flesh.//

Time seems to stop.

Augustin's eyes find <<if $doctor >> you <<else>> Father Benoît<</if>> desperate and heart breaking. "DO SOMETHING!" 

You can't move. Can't speak. Can't do anything but stand there while the truth settles over you like a stone thrown in a lake.

Moon above.
You did //this//.
You killed her. You killed Jeanne Boulet.

//Shit//

[[Shit is right.|EndofDemo]]




