[[Next|woodend]]


:: woodend {"position":"1450,450","size":"100,100"}
The sun is still low on the horizon. You see its shining rays slice through the canopy scattering gold across the forest floor. The earth is soft beneath your feet. With the way the morning dew clings to the leaves and how strong the smell of petrichor is, you assume it rained last night.
You try to walk on stones, roots and solid ground rather than the soft muddy earth, knowing the latter would leave a trace. Testing each step before putting your weight down, trying not to sink, trying not to leave a mark that will betray you to anyone looking.

You hear a sound above and feel your heart leap into your throat, before realising it is just a squirrel darting across branches. You exhale slowly, and march on.
You catch a glimmer of the river through the trees. You only need to follow it to reach the village.

You skirt the muddier banks, stepping where the soil is firmer. Your soles sting from hidden stones and thorns, but there’s no other way. Besides, Now, it's just a matter of not being seen, you can always claim you came to wash. Still, you're hyper alert to every sound and smell around you, every rustle, every snap of twigs sends your pulse racing. 
The forest hums and shifts around you, alive and watchful, <<if $stress ==  0>>judging you, <<elseif $stress >= 1 >>oblivious to your struggle, <<endif>>while you try to weave your way silently towards the faint promise of safety at the edge of the trees.

[[Finally, you manage to reach your destination. |home1]]


